Sorry, I have not noticed this tracker until doing cleanup for 
the DbUnit 2.1 release. XML parsers normalizes CRLF 
sequences to be just LF, so that it can be used cross-
platform. I'm reluctant to systematically escape CRLF; 
sometimes it might be desirable to keep original CRLF 
sequences while in other times it might not. 

I rather suggest that you decorate the exported dataset with 
ReplacementDataSet like this:

IDataSet originalDataSet = connection.createDataSet\(\);
ReplacementDataSet replacementDataSet = new 
ReplacementDataSet\(originalDataSet\);
replacementDataSet.addReplacementSubstring
\("\r\n", "&amp;\#13;&amp;\#10;"\);

FlatXmlWriter xmlWriter = new FlatXmlWriter\(out\);
xmlWriter.write\(replacementDataSet\);

Let me know if you find this solution acceptable.

