The following code comes from the DatabaseTestCase 
class.
As we can see in the finally clause, the current 
connection is always closed.

This makes it impossible for one to subclass 
DatabaseTestCase in order to make the current 
connection remain active during execution of a 
TestSuite in order for all testcases to use the same 
reusable connection.

I subclassed DatabaseTestCase so that each testcase 
can become "aware" if it's being executed as a single 
test or part of a testsuit.

In case of a single test I want my baseclass to close the 
connection at the end.

In case of a testsuit I don't want each testcase to close 
the current connection, instead I want my testsuit 
baseclass to close the connection when appropriate.

\----
private void executeOperation\(
DatabaseOperation operation\)
throws Exception \{

if \(operation \!= DatabaseOperation.NONE\) \{
IDatabaseConnection connection = getConnection\(\);
try \{
operation.execute\(connection, getDataSet\(\)\);
\} finally \{
closeConnection\(connection\);
\}
\}

\}
\----    

closeConnection\(\) should only be called depending on a 
settable boolean flag like this:

...
\} finally \{
if \(DO\_CLOSE\_CONNECTION\) \{
closeConnection\(connection\);
\}
\}
...

