tickets.description:
There is a problem with org.dbunit.util.xml.XmlWriter class. When XmlWriter needs to surround data with a CDATA section and there are CDATA sections already in the data, then XmlWriter.writeCData\(\) method generates invalid XML.

The cause of the problem is that CDATA sections can't be nested - you can't have \]\]&gt; inside a CDATA section. The solutions is to replace any occurrence of \]\]&gt; in the data by \]\]\]\]&gt;&lt;\!\[CDATA\[&gt;, so that the new top level CDATA section is split into many valid CDATA sections.

This is how I fixed this problem:

public XmlWriter writeCData\(String cdata\) throws IOException
\{
closeOpeningTag\(\);

// There may already be CDATA sections inside the data.
// But CDATA sections can't be nested - can't have \]\]&gt; inside a CDATA section.
// The solutions is to replace any occurrence of \]\]&gt; by \]\]\]\]&gt;&lt;\!\[CDATA\[&gt;,
// so that the top CDATA section is split into many valid CDATA sections.
cdata = cdata.replaceAll\("\]\]&gt;", "\]\]\]\]&gt;&lt;\!\[CDATA\[&gt;"\);

this.empty = false;
this.wroteText = true;
this.out.write\("&lt;\!\[CDATA\["\);
this.out.write\(cdata\);
this.out.write\("\]\]&gt;"\);
return this;
\}

Regards,
Andrzej

