Apparently, the code which produces a RowOutOfBoundsException in the AbstractTable class is reporting that x&gt;x when it should be reporting x&gt;=x as a problem.

This is the code in question:

protected void assertValidRowIndex\(int row, int rowCount\)
throws DataSetException
\{
if \(row &lt; 0\)
\{
throw new RowOutOfBoundsException\(row + " &lt; 0"\);
\}

if \(row &gt;= rowCount\)
\{
throw new RowOutOfBoundsException\(row + " &gt; " + rowCount\);
\}
\}

From org.dbunit.dataset.AbstractTable

The solution is rather simple, change the text in the second exception to show &gt;= rather than &gt; and everything should be ok.

