When using an inline DTD which has more than only a few elements in it, I get a NullPointerException in org\dbunit\dataset\xml\FlatDtdProducer.java at line 224. Of course, this is a bug. I have already fixed it. The bug is in the Method endDTD\(\) which did not take into account that a table name may be surrounded by brackets. The correct patched version of this method is included below with comments explaining the details of this bug. The whole file containing the patch is attached to this bug report.

public void endDTD\(\) throws SAXException \{
try \{
if \(\_rootModel \!= null\) \{
// Remove enclosing model parenthesis
final String rootModel = \_rootModel.substring\(1, \_rootModel.length\(\) - 1\);

// Parse the root element model to determine the table sequence.
// Support all sequence or choices model but not the mix of both.
final String delim = \(rootModel.indexOf\(","\) \!= -1\) ? "," : "|";
final StringTokenizer tokenizer = new StringTokenizer\(rootModel, delim\);
while \(tokenizer.hasMoreTokens\(\)\) \{
String table = tokenizer.nextToken\(\);

// Prune ending occurrence operator
if \(table.endsWith\("\*"\) || table.endsWith\("?"\) || table.endsWith\("+"\)\) \{
table = table.substring\(0, table.length\(\) - 1\);
\}

					// Interestingly, sometimes a table comes in brackets, e.g. "\(mytablename\)"
					// These must be removed because otherwise the list of columns associated with the table
					// can not be retrieved from the map, i.e. the list of columns \(columnList\) is null.
					// This leads to a NullPointerException in DB-Unit 2.2 when columnList is being accessed.
					// Patch for NullPointerException starts here
if \(table.startsWith\("\("\)\) \{
table = table.substring\(1, table.length\(\) - 1\);
\}

if \(table.endsWith\("\)"\)\) \{
table = table.substring\(0, table.length\(\) - 1\);
\}
// Patch for NullPointerException ends here

final List columnList = \(List\) \_columnListMap.get\(table\);
final Column\[\] columns = \(Column\[\]\) columnList.toArray\(new Column\[0\]\);

\_consumer.startTable\(new DefaultTableMetaData\(table, columns\)\);
\_consumer.endTable\(\);
\}
\}

\_consumer.endDataSet\(\);
\}
catch \(DataSetException e\) \{
throw new SAXException\(e\);
\}
\}

