Alrighty, it turns out the problem was a bit more complex than I thought.

Turns out that in a more complex dtd, it's fairly rare to have tags that just have a single bracket and a single operator on them- structures like the following are common:

\(table1,\(table2,table3+\)?\)+

With the current code, table1 and table2 get correctly parsed, but table3 does not- because only one character is trimmed off the end, we end up with "table3+\)?\)" as our table name, which still fails to match the key for columnList and causes the dreaded NullPointerException.

Anyway, I've had a play, and I've come up with a solution that seems to work \(not too elegant, but meh\):

From FlatDtdProducer.java Line 262 -  

while \(tokenizer.hasMoreTokens\(\)\) \{
String tableName = cleanupTableName\(tokenizer.nextToken\(\)\);

List columnList = \(List\)\_columnListMap.get\(tableName\);
Column\[\] columns = \(Column\[\]\)columnList.toArray\(new Column\[0\]\);

\_consumer.startTable\(new DefaultTableMetaData\(tableName, columns\)\);
\_consumer.endTable\(\);
\}

Note that the old code for cleaning the table name is gone...

This is supported by the following method:

protected String cleanupTableName\(String tableName\) \{
String cleaned = tableName;
while \(cleaned.startsWith\("\("\)\) \{
cleaned = cleaned.substring\(1\);
\}
while \(cleaned.endsWith\("\)"\)
|| cleaned.endsWith\("\*"\)
|| cleaned.endsWith\("?"\)
|| cleaned.endsWith\("+"\)\) \{
cleaned = cleaned.substring\(0, cleaned.length\(\) - 1\);
\}
return cleaned;
\}

And verified in the test case like so:

public void testCleanupTableName\(\) \{
FlatDtdProducer producer = new FlatDtdProducer\(null\);
assertEquals\(
"Make sure a start bracketed table is cleaned",
"table",
producer.cleanupTableName\("\(table"\)\);
assertEquals\(
"Make sure an end bracketed table is cleaned",
"table",
producer.cleanupTableName\("table\)"\)\);
assertEquals\(
"Make sure tables with multiple control characters are cleaned",
"table",
producer.cleanupTableName\("\(table+\)?"\)\);
assertEquals\(
"Make sure multi-nested tables at the start of a group"
\+ " are cleaned",
"table",
producer.cleanupTableName\("\(\(table?\)+\)"\)\);
\}

Files attached\!
File Added: FlatDtdProducer.java

