This issue is somewhat related to \#1344618. As far as I can see this problem occurs only for TINYINT\(1\). I did the following test which brings up astonishing results:

Connection conn = getConnection\(\);
DatabaseConnection dbConn = new DatabaseConnection\(conn, "test"\);
dbConn.getConfig\(\).setProperty\(DatabaseConfig.PROPERTY\_DATATYPE\_FACTORY, new MySqlDataTypeFactory\(\)\);

// DatabaseDataSet - uses DatabaseTableMetaData \(interally java.sql.DatabaseMetaData\)
ITableMetaData md = dbConn.createDataSet\(\).getTableMetaData\("mytab"\);
System.out.println\(md.getColumns\(\)\[0\]\);
// ForwardOnlyResultSetTable - uses ResultSetTableMetaData \(internally java.sql.ResultSetMetaData\)
ITable t = dbConn.createTable\("mytab"\); // same as "createQueryTable"
System.out.println\(t.getTableMetaData\(\).getColumns\(\)\[0\]\);

