When the following query is used to create a table in Interbase: 'create table "abc" \(&lt;...columns...&gt;\)', the table columns then must be queried with literally the same expression which was used to create a table. So, to get all the columns from the table with quoted name in Interbase, you have to write something like
DatabaseMetaData md = c.getMetaData\(\);
md.getColumns\(null, null, "\"abc\"", "%"\);
Please note these additional double quotes. \(If you omit them, no columns will be returned\).
I could not find a way how to determine whether table was created with double-quotes or not, as getTables\(\) returns table name with no quotes in any case. In my patch, I suggest the following straightforward approach: programmer may turn on additional double quotes in places like getColumns\(\) using the DatabaseConfig's feature. I tested it for getColumns\(\) in my application, and it worked.

