Hi, unfortunately, I'm seeing the same behaviour with the snapshot as well.

I am in fact using QueryDataSet.addTable\(tableName, query\) with the query parameter. Here's the excerpt:

QueryDataSet actual = new QueryDataSet\(connection\);
SqlResultComparisonData comparison = getComparisonData\(\);
XmlDataSet expected = getExpectedDataSet\(comparison\);
for \(ComparisonSqlData sqlData : comparison.getComparisonSqls\(\)\)
\{
actual.addTable\(sqlData.getTableName\(\), sqlData.getSql\(\)\);
\}

Assertion.assertEquals\(expected, actual\);

Now the problem is that assertEquals\(\) iterates over all expected tables and for EVERY table in the expected dataset it also iterates over EVERY table in the actual \(query\) data set, resulting in the fact that it pulls out every table from the set, eventhough it only needs one table at a time. The constructor "AbstractResultSetTable\(String tableName, String selectStatement, IDatabaseConnection connection\) throws DataSetException, SQLException" always ends up getting called.

In QueryTableIterator.getTable\(\) I always fall into this part of the code \(inside else\):

DatabaseConfig config = \_connection.getConfig\(\);
IResultSetTableFactory factory = \(IResultSetTableFactory\)config.getProperty\(
DatabaseConfig.PROPERTY\_RESULTSET\_TABLE\_FACTORY\);

\_currentTable = factory.createTable\(entry.getTableName\(\), entry.getQuery\(\), \_connection\);


Now, if this is the correct behaviour without using caching wrappers, then I guess the problem could be fixed by reducing the number of iterations Assertion.equals\(\)?

Hi and thanks for your response.

I think the root cause \(you already mentioned initially\) is the "AbstractDataSet.getTable\(String tableName\)" method which creates a new Iterator object in every invocation and ALWAYS iterates over the whole dataset \(this is apparently necessary to detect duplicate/ambiguous table names\). So the only thing that I can recommend to you is to wrap your QueryDataSet with a org.dbunit.dataset.CachedDataSet which should avoid reloading the data x^2 times \(where x is the table-count\). Here is a sample code:

QueryDataSet actual = new QueryDataSet\(connection\);
SqlResultComparisonData comparison = getComparisonData\(\);
XmlDataSet expected = getExpectedDataSet\(comparison\);
for \(ComparisonSqlData sqlData : comparison.getComparisonSqls\(\)\)
\{
actual.addTable\(sqlData.getTableName\(\), sqlData.getSql\(\)\);
\}

CachedDataSet actualCached = new CachedDataSet\(actual\);
Assertion.assertEquals\(expected, actualCached\);

Hope this helps.

Regards,
mat

