As discussed with Ilya on the users mailing list he has the need to preserve \r\n character sequences when exporting data from the database into XML. This is why he needs the possibility to extend CDATA and normal text written by the XmlDataSetWriter.

For details see discussion at 

https://sourceforge.net/mailarchive/forum.php?thread\_name=a0671cbd0901170428h576f574bm7306f2955c744015%40mail.gmail.com&forum\_name=dbunit-user


Ilya actually needs to extend the new 2 methods as follows:

protected void writeValueCData\(String stringValue\) throws IOException
\{
int k = 0;
while\(\(k = str.indexOf\('\r'\)\) \!= -1\)\{
getXmlWriter\(\).writeCData\(str.substring\(0, k\)\);
getXmlWriter\(\).writeText\("\r", true\);
str = str.substring\(k + 1\);
\}
getXmlWriter\(\).writeCData\(str\);
\}

protected void writeValue\(String stringValue\) throws IOException
\{
// Write literally
super.getXmlWriter\(\).writeText\(stringValue, true\);
\}

