I am extending DBTestCase and based on a fix in 2.4.3 for issue 2023994 I overrided the method DatabaseTestCase.setUpDatabaseConfig\(DatabaseConfig config\) \(in the issue method "DatabaseTestCase.setUpConnectionConfig\(DatabaseConfig config\)" is mentioned by Gomma, I think that's a typo\).

Problem is that my overridden method is never called. So my code is never executed:
	protected void setUpDatabaseConfig\(DatabaseConfig config\) \{
		config.setProperty\(DatabaseConfig.PROPERTY\_DATATYPE\_FACTORY, new Oracle10DataTypeFactory\(\)\);
		config.setProperty\(DatabaseConfig.PROPERTY\_TABLE\_TYPE, new String\[\] \{ "TABLE", "VIEW" \}\);
	\}

After some debugging I discovered the following:

DatabaseTestCase.setUpDatabaseConfig\(DatabaseConfig config\) is called ONLY in DatabaseTestCase.newDatabaseTester\(\):
protected IDatabaseTester newDatabaseTester\(\) throws Exception\{
logger.debug\("newDatabaseTester\(\) - start"\);

final IDatabaseConnection connection = getConnection\(\);
setUpDatabaseConfig\(connection.getConfig\(\)\);
final IDatabaseTester tester = new DefaultDatabaseTester\(connection\);
return tester;
\}

BUT DBTestCase has overridden this method:
protected IDatabaseTester newDatabaseTester\(\) throws Exception \{
return new PropertiesBasedJdbcDatabaseTester\(\);
\}

Which doesn't call setUpDatabaseConfig\!
I am basing my code on the examples on http://dbunit.sourceforge.net/howto.html extend from DBTestCase.


thanks Armand

