Somewhere between 2.1 and 2.4.4 following change was done in the XlsTable.java - for cells of the numeric type now result of getNumericValue\(cell\) function is returned instead of new BigDecimal\(cell.getNumericCellValue\).
This function checks cell for formatting and, if formatting is not general or text \("@"\) then new BigDecimal\(String.valueOf\(cellValue\)\);
is returned. This result in big decimals with different string representation, e.g. if cell contains value 666666 then older DBUnit version creates BigDecimal which toString\(\) method returns "666666" and newer version returns BigDecimal with toString\(\) returning "666666.0". And if value is intended for a character column in DB - old and new version become incompatible.

